In early March of 1945, the Polish 1st Army with elements of the Soviet 3rd Shock Army and the 1st Guards Tank Army annihilated the German X. SS-Armeekorps and inflicted serious casualties on the Korpsgruppe von Tettau, which managed to break through Soviet troops along with many civilians.
